name: The Temptation Dabolim - 24x7 Complete Food Shop

reviews.review_text:
Temptation is my last-minute go-to place for a range of cravings. Located on the Vasco-Verna/Airport road, it’s an affordable and convenient stop for a quick bite. I’ve been here multiple times, and while the pricing is reasonable, the food quality matches what you pay for. It’s not the most delicious out there, but it’s decent, with consistency at a good 80-90% of the time.

Speaking specifically about this outlet, the staff experience is mixed—50% are diligent and maintain hygiene, while the other 50% seem indifferent, either bored or working just for the paycheck. You can tell from their demeanor and lack of attention to cleanliness. Management should take this seriously, as this outlet has potential, but a few careless staff members could tarnish the brand’s reputation.

I’ve noticed unclean tables and cockroaches on multiple occasions(Top Section), and poor hygiene practices among some kitchen staff. This needs urgent attention to improve the overall experience.

If you want to experience the best of Temptation, I’d recommend visiting their Margao store instead.

A short walk from the airport,

Delicious food at affordable prices, if you have some time to kill at the airport then I would definitely recommend this place.

All items are priced reasonably. They have baguettes, soft rolls, sandwiches,cheesecakes, cakes ,snacks , coffee,tea..etc...all priced between 20-200

From the sitting area you can spot Indian Air force jets, helicopters.

Visited twice, tried cinnamon carrot cake and blueberry cheesecake. Both excellent and delicious and just the right amount pf sweet. Pleasantly surprised with the place.

They don't have a lot of coffee options (like cappuccino etc) just basic machine coffee (even cold coffee is from a dispenser) but it's decent.

description:
**The Temptation Dabolim - 24x7 Complete Food Shop: Culinary Convenience at the Goan Gateway**

Nestled conveniently on the Vasco-Verna/Airport road in Bogmalo, The Temptation Dabolim operates round-the-clock, providing travelers and locals alike with reliable comfort food options. Garnering a commendable rating of 4.1 from over 812 diners, this eatery, often deemed a 24-hour food shop, stands out for its affordability and wide-ranging menu, but customer feedback highlights mixed sentiments regarding cleanliness and service.

**Ambiance & Design**  
As you step into The Temptation, you're greeted by a casual yet functional ambiance—ideal for a quick snack before catching a flight or winding down after a long journey. The tables, while sometimes criticized for their cleanliness, boast a straightforward design with a rustic charm typical of a Goan eatery. The layout is inviting, and a few snapshots reflect a cozy seating area where guests can catch a glimpse of Indian Air Force jets and helicopters overhead, adding an interesting backdrop to your meal. 

Visual highlights from customer photos illustrate the bustling environment with bright, well-lit spaces, albeit dotted with areas that could benefit from a thorough cleaning, as many reviews noted the presence of bugs that detracted from the experience.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  
The Temptation excels in offering a wide variety of bakery items and quick bites ranging from baguettes, soft rolls, and sandwiches to decadent desserts like cinnamon carrot cake and blueberry cheesecake. A review noted their pastries were absolutely delightful, perfectly sweetened and expertly crafted. With most items priced between ₹20 to ₹200, it’s a budget-friendly stop with decent culinary offerings. However, one downside mentioned was the limited coffee selection—predominantly basic machine options—implying a need for broader beverage diversity.

Moreover, while the quality of food generally aligns with the prices, some customers have pointed out inconsistencies, suggesting that while you might find a superb dessert one day, another visit could yield a more mediocre experience.

**Customer Experience & Service**  
Service at The Temptation appears to be a mixed bag, with staff demeanor varying widely between diligent service and distinct indifference. Certain reviews echoed concerns regarding hygiene practices, with mentions of unclean tables and staff members demonstrating a careless attitude. It seems the management needs to focus on enhancing service quality to ensure a consistently pleasant experience for all diners. 

For those around the airport area, especially travelers with a bit of time to spare, the restaurant’s policies appear welcoming to both walk-ins and reservations, making it a convenient stop.

**Popularity & Reviews**  
Overall, customer sentiment at The Temptation blends affection for its affordability and culinary convenience with frustration over hygiene issues. While it's recognized for its accessibility—earning noteworthy mentions as a close-quarters option for airport travelers—there’s a looming need for improvements in cleanliness and service standards to leverage its full potential. Social media buzz reveals a mix of satisfied pastry lovers alongside concerned patrons advocating for restaurant management to take hygiene more seriously.

**Utilizing Visual Content**  
Customer-provided photos help paint a well-rounded picture of The Temptation Dabolim—illustrating an accessible dining spot filled with enticing food options while also highlighting areas of concern that require attention. The images showcase desserts that tempt the taste buds and a seating area that, despite its charm, could shine brighter with routine upkeep.
 
In conclusion, The Temptation Dabolim presents a unique blend of convenience and comfort food set within a bustling airport backdrop, but it’s clear from reviews that addressing hygiene issues and enhancing service quality could transform this eatery from a last-minute stop into a must-visit culinary gem.
